data.title: Newark Public Schools' reality shows "Newark Fashion Forward" and "Newark Chops" to stream on In The Black Network from October 31st, reaching national audiences.
data.description: Today, Newark Public Schools revealed that its reality series, "Newark Fashion Forward" and "Newark Chops," will debut on a new entertainment platform, reaching national audiences. This announcement was made in Newark, N.J., on Oct. 30, 2025. The series will premiere on In The..., expanding their reach beyond local viewers. This move signifies a strategic effort to showcase the talent and creativity within Newark Public Schools to a wider audience.

data.title: Omega Healthcare Investors reported Q3 2025 net income of $185 million (compared to $115 million in Q3 2024) and Adjusted FFO of $243 million.
data.description: Omega Healthcare Investors, Inc. shared its quarterly results for the period ending September 30, 2025. The company reported a net income of $185 million, equivalent to $0.59 per diluted share, surpassing the previous year's $115 million, or $0.42 per diluted share for Q3 2024. Adjusted Funds From Operations ("Adjusted FFO" or "AFFO") for the quarter amounted to $243 million, or $0.79 per diluted share. The results were based on 308 million weighted average shares outstanding.

data.title: EquipmentShare introduces Team Orange, a volunteer corps for hurricane response, involving ex-military & first responders.
data.description: In Columbia, Missouri, EquipmentShare, a prominent provider of connected jobsite technology and a major equipment rental company in the U.S., has introduced Team Orange. This initiative is a volunteer corps financed by the company that aims to enhance community resilience and disaster preparedness. Launched this summer, the program is designed to equip employees, particularly those with military and first-responder experience, with essential skills. Team Orange is part of EquipmentShare's ongoing efforts to contribute to society and strengthen its corporate culture.

data.title: Arthur J. Gallagher & Co. announces Q3 2025 financial results; Brokerage reported $2.93B revenues, Risk Management $402.1M, Corporate $0.4M. Total company: $3.33B revenues reported, $604.9M net earnings, $1.02B EBITDAC, $2.32 earnings per share. Acquisition of AssuredPartners for $13.8B, raised cash through stock offering and senior notes issuance. Compensation expense & ratios adjusted, net earnings and adjusted EBITDAC margins provided. Acquisition activity: 6 closed in Q3 2025, estimated annualized revenues acquired $3.04B. Full details on Benzinga.com.
data.description: Arthur J. Gallagher & Co. reported its financial results for Q3 2025, with revenues reaching $3.33 billion, a significant increase from $2.76 billion in Q3 2024. Net earnings for Q3 2025 were $273.6 million, lower than the $314.1 million in Q3 2024. Adjusted EBITDAC showed growth at $1.02 billion in Q3 2025 compared to $811.1 million in Q3 2024. The company reported growth in both its Brokerage and Risk Management segments. Brokerage segment revenue climbed to $2.93 billion from $2.39 billion in Q3 2024, while Risk Management segment revenue saw an increase to $401.9 million from $368.1 million. The company closed six acquisitions in Q3 2025 with estimated annualized revenues acquired at $3.03 billion. AssuredPartners was acquired for approximately $13.8 billion in August 2025, financing it through a common stock offering and senior notes issuance. Gallagher's client-centric approach and growth strategies are credited for the positive financial performance. Organic revenue growth was at 4.8%, and the company highlighted strong revenue growth from acquisitions. CEO J. Patrick Gallagher, Jr. expressed satisfaction with the quarter's performance and the successful integration of AssuredPartners into their operations. Compensation expenses and ratios were analyzed, with adjusted ratios showing improvement. Operating expenses also grew, but the company maintained a strong financial position. The complete article is available on Benzinga.com.

data.title: COPT Defense buys 142,000 sq ft building in Chantilly, VA for $40.2M, fully occupied by top US Defense Contractor.
data.description: In Columbia, Maryland, COPT Defense Properties (NYSE: CDP) recently disclosed its purchase of Stonegate I, a Class A office building spanning 142,000 square feet located at 15050 Conference Center Drive in Chantilly, VA. This acquisition amounted to a total of $40.2 million. The office building is currently fully leased by a leading U.S. Defense Contractor, holding a spot in the top 20, with a decade left on their lease agreement. This property marks the ninth location within the Company's portfolio. Stonegate I's construction was completed in 2XXX.
